===Social responsibility===
Adobe promotes several ongoing social responsibility initiatives, including [http://youthvoices.adobe.com/ Adobe Youth Voices] and [http://www.adobe.com/corporate-responsibility/community/creativity-scholarship.html Creativity Scholarships] through the Adobe Foundation.<ref>[http://www.adobe.com/corporate-responsibility.html Adobe Corporate Responsibility]. Adobe.com. Retrieved on 2013-07-21.</ref><ref>[http://www.guidestar.org/organizations/85-0442799/adobe-foundation.aspx Nonprofit Report for ADOBE FOUNDATION INC]. Guidestar.org. Retrieved on 2013-07-21.</ref>

As part of its Lehi, Utah, campus construction, Adobe supported an Artist In Residence program at [http://www.thanksgivingpoint.org Thanksgiving Point Institute], in which artist [http://www.andrewsmithart.com/ Andrew Smith] constructed a kinetic sculpture to be placed in the new Adobe campus building.<ref>[http://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/arts-and-theatre/visual/thanksgiving-point-artist-creating-sculpture-for-adobe-campus/article_ad0456c0-d47b-509b-823a-90ec74ca0b5d.html Thanksgiving Point artist creating sculpture for Adobe campus : The Ticket]. Heraldextra.com (2012-08-26). Retrieved on 2013-07-21.</ref><ref>[http://dev.utahbusiness.com/articles/view/thanksgiving_point_and_adobe_promote_new_artist_in Utah Business]. Dev.utahbusiness.com (2012-08-07). Retrieved on 2013-07-21.</ref>

==Employee relations==
A [[class-action lawsuit]] alleging that the company suppressed employee compensation has been filed against Adobe in a California federal district court.<ref>[http://online.wsj.com/article/BT-CO-20131025-706737.html Judge Grants Class-Action Status in Silicon Valley Hiring Suit - WSJ.com]. Online.wsj.com (2013-10-25). Retrieved on 2013-10-30.</ref>

==Public relations==
Adobe ranked no. 5 on a list of ''Internet’s 9 Most Hated Companies'', based on a 2013 survey on [[Reddit.com]].<ref>[http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/08/20/the-internet-s-9-most-hated-companies.html The Internet’s 9 Most Hated Companies - The Daily Beast | Business]</ref> Adobe's [[Adobe Reader|Reader]] and [[Adobe Flash|Flash]] have been listed on ''The 10 most hated programs of all time'' on [[TechRadar.com]].<ref>[http://www.techradar.com/news/software/applications/the-10-most-hated-programs-of-all-time-1060129 The 10 most hated programs of all time | TechRadar]</ref> According to commentators Adobe's [[Public Relations|PR]] deteriorated after the company introduced the [[Creative Cloud]] subscription only licensing model.<ref>[http://www.gotransverse.com/transverseblog/Adobe-subscription-disaster Adobe’s Public Relations Disaster | Transverse]</ref>

A [[class-action lawsuit]] leveling claims of [[unfair business practices]] and [[breach of contract]] related to a massive security breach has been filed against Adobe in a California federal court.<ref>[http://www.lexisnexis.com/legalnewsroom/mealeys/b/newsheadlines/archive/2013/11/13/putative-class-action-filed-over-adobe-systems-security-breach.aspx Putative Class Action Filed Over Adobe Systems Security Breach | LexisNexis]</ref>

